        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 6:21PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Clarkesville, or near Demorest, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Demorest, Clarkesville, Raoul, Baldwin, Mount Airy, Alto, and
Cornelia.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
